Fig_5_shared_genera

Erin Dahl and Lisa Karstens, PhD

2022-03-10

  • Purpose
  • Load Libraries and Data
  • Overall number of taxonomic classifications for vaginal microbiome
  • Overall number of taxonomic classifications for bladder microbiome
  • Number of overall Genera shared
  • Venn Diagram
  • Shared genera

Purpose

To understand and compare the shared and unique genera in the vaginal and bladder microbiomes and document the analysis present in the manuscript Network-based differences in the vaginal and bladder microbial communities between women with and without urgency urinary incontinence by Nardos et al.

Load Libraries and Data

library(here)
library(phyloseq)
library(tidyverse)
library(kableExtra)
library(VennDiagram)
library(gridExtra)

# load data
load(here("data", "sufu_tree_ps_rel.RData"))

Melt phyloseq

mdf_vs_pre <-psmelt(ps_vs_rel)

mdf_ur_pre <-psmelt(ps_ur_rel)

Overall number of taxonomic classifications for vaginal microbiome

  • Unique Phylum : 8
  • Unique Class : 12
  • Unique Order : 18
  • Unique Family : 31
  • Unique Genus : 66

Three most abundant genera: Lactobacillus, Gardnerella, Prevotella

vs_tax <- mdf_vs_pre %>% select( Abundance, Phylum, Class, Order, Family, Genus) %>% 
              filter( Abundance > 0) %>%
              unique() 

# Number of unique Phylum
length(unique(vs_tax$Phylum))
## [1] 8
# Number of unique Class
length(unique(vs_tax$Class))
## [1] 12
# Number of unique Order
length(unique(vs_tax$Order))
## [1] 18
# Number of unique Family
length(unique(vs_tax$Family))
## [1] 31
# Number of unique Genus
length(unique(vs_tax$Genus))
## [1] 66
# top 3 abundant bacteria
top_abund_vs <- vs_tax %>% group_by(Genus) %>% summarise(sum_abundance = sum(Abundance)) %>% arrange(desc(sum_abundance))
print("Top abundant bacteria in vaginal microbiome: ")
## [1] "Top abundant bacteria in vaginal microbiome: "
top_abund_vs$Genus[1:3]
## [1] "Lactobacillus" "Gardnerella"   "Prevotella"

Overall number of taxonomic classifications for bladder microbiome

  • Unique Phylum : 14
  • Unique Class : 21
  • Unique Order : 43
  • Unique Family : 70
  • Unique Genus : 131

Three most abundant genera: Lactobacillus, Bacteroides, Prevotellaceae_UCG-001

Number of overall Genera shared

For Genus Level evaluation

  • Case: 44 bladder, 33 both, 20 vaginal
  • Control: 80 bladder, 33 both, 17 vaginal

How many bladder bacteria are shared with the vaginal microbiome?

  • Case: 33/77, 43%
  • Control: 33/113, 29%
case_vs <- mdf_vs_pre %>% unique() %>%
              select( subject_id, Abundance, Phylum, Genus, cohort_sufu) %>%
              filter( Abundance > 0) %>%
              filter(cohort_sufu == "case")%>%
              drop_na() %>%
              mutate(Phylum_Genus = paste(Phylum, Genus)) %>%
              group_by(Phylum_Genus) %>%
              summarize(Abundance_mean = mean(Abundance), Abundance_median= round(median(Abundance), 2)) %>%
              mutate(new_col = Phylum_Genus) %>% 
              separate(new_col, c("Phylum", "Genus"), " ")

control_vs <- mdf_vs_pre %>% unique() %>%
              select( subject_id, Abundance, Phylum, Genus, cohort_sufu) %>%
              filter( Abundance > 0) %>%
              filter(cohort_sufu == "control")%>%
              drop_na() %>%
              mutate(Phylum_Genus = paste(Phylum, Genus)) %>%
              group_by(Phylum_Genus) %>%
              summarize(Abundance_mean = mean(Abundance), Abundance_median= round(median(Abundance), 2)) %>%
              mutate(new_col = Phylum_Genus) %>% 
              separate(new_col, c("Phylum", "Genus"), " ")

case_ur <- mdf_ur_pre%>% unique() %>%
              select( subject_id, Abundance, Phylum, Genus, cohort_sufu) %>%
              filter( Abundance > 0) %>%
              filter(cohort_sufu == "case")%>%
              drop_na() %>%
              mutate(Phylum_Genus = paste(Phylum, Genus)) %>%
              group_by(Phylum_Genus) %>%
              summarize(Abundance_mean = mean(Abundance), Abundance_median= round(median(Abundance), 2)) %>%
              mutate(new_col = Phylum_Genus) %>% 
              separate(new_col, c("Phylum", "Genus"), " ")

control_ur <- mdf_ur_pre%>% unique() %>%
              select( subject_id, Abundance, Phylum, Genus, cohort_sufu) %>%
              filter( Abundance > 0) %>%
              filter(cohort_sufu == "control") %>%
              drop_na() %>%
              mutate(Phylum_Genus = paste(Phylum, Genus)) %>%
              group_by(Phylum_Genus) %>%
              summarize(Abundance_mean = mean(Abundance), Abundance_median= round(median(Abundance), 2)) %>%
              mutate(new_col = Phylum_Genus) %>% 
              separate(new_col, c("Phylum", "Genus"), " ")

# find vaginal Genus names
case_vs_g <- unique(case_vs$Genus)
control_vs_g <- unique(control_vs$Genus)

# find bladder Genus names
case_ur_g <- unique(case_ur$Genus)
control_ur_g <- unique(control_ur$Genus)

# find shared Genus
case_both_g <-intersect(case_vs_g, case_ur_g)
control_both_g <-intersect(control_vs_g, control_ur_g)

case_ur_only_g <- length(case_ur_g)- length(case_both_g)
case_vs_only_g <- length(case_vs_g)- length(case_both_g)

# Case/UUI
case_ur_only_g
## [1] 44
length(case_both_g)
## [1] 33
case_vs_only_g
## [1] 20
control_ur_only_g <- length(control_ur_g)- length(control_both_g)
control_vs_only_g <- length(control_vs_g)- length(control_both_g)

# Control
control_ur_only_g
## [1] 80
length(control_both_g)
## [1] 33
control_vs_only_g
## [1] 17
# How many bladder bacteria are shared with the vaginal microbiome?
# Case/UUI
length(case_both_g)/ length(case_ur$Genus)
## [1] 0.4285714
# Control
length(control_both_g)/ length(control_ur$Genus)
## [1] 0.2920354

Venn Diagram

mdf_ur_pre <- mdf_ur_pre %>% drop_na()
mdf_vs_pre <- mdf_vs_pre %>% drop_na()

 # Bladder and vaginal genera bacteria for cases

 plot_cases <-   venn.diagram(
    x = list(
      mdf_ur_pre %>%
        filter(cohort_sufu == "case",
               Abundance > 0) %>%
        distinct(Genus) %>%
        pull(Genus),
      mdf_vs_pre %>%
        filter(cohort_sufu == "case",
               Abundance > 0) %>%
        distinct(Genus) %>%
        pull(Genus)
    ),
    category.names = c("Urinary", "Vaginal"),
    filename = NULL,
    main = "UUI",
    main.cex = 3,

    # Numbers
    cex = 3,

    # Set names
    cat.cex = 3,
    cat.pos = c(-27, 27),
    cat.dist = c(0.055, 0.055)
  )
  

# Bladder and vaginal genera bacteria for controls
plot_ctrl <-  venn.diagram(
    x = list(
      mdf_ur_pre %>%
        filter(cohort_sufu == "control",
               Abundance > 0) %>%
        distinct(Genus) %>%
        pull(Genus),
      mdf_vs_pre %>%
        filter(cohort_sufu == "control",
               Abundance > 0) %>%
        distinct(Genus) %>%
        pull(Genus)
    ),
    category.names = c("Urinary", "Vaginal"),
    filename = NULL,
    main = "Controls",
    main.cex = 3,

    # Numbers
    cex = 3,

    # Set names
    cat.cex = 3,
    cat.pos = c(-27, 27),
    cat.dist = c(0.055, 0.055)
  )

grid.arrange(gTree(children=plot_cases), gTree(children=plot_ctrl), ncol=2)

Shared genera

# Control
control_vs_shared <- control_vs %>% filter(Genus %in% control_both_g) %>% 
                      select(-Abundance_mean)  %>% 
                      rename( vs_median = Abundance_median)
control_ur_shared <- control_ur %>% filter(Genus %in% control_both_g) %>% 
                      select(-Abundance_mean)  %>% 
                      rename(ur_median = Abundance_median)

control_shared_taxa <- merge(control_vs_shared, control_ur_shared, by = c("Phylum_Genus", "Phylum" ,"Genus"))


control_shared_taxa %>% 
  kbl() %>%
  add_header_above(c("Table of shared genera in controls" = 5)) %>%
  kable_styling(full_width = F) %>%
  kable_material(c("striped", "hover"))
